description: Built in 1912, this beautiful home exudes elegance and is a true gem in one of San Francisco's most desirable neighborhoods. The main level features a spacious living room with fireplace and lovely outlooks. The formal dining room offers period built-ins, intricate moldings, and overlooks the private tiered backyard with deck and patio. Bright updated kitchen with a breakfast bar, Thermador appliances and ample storage. A half bathroom off the kitchen completes this floor. The upper level opens to three generously-sized bedrooms and two bathrooms. The primary bedroom consists of an impressive walk-in closet and bathroom with double vanity and dual shower. The two additional bedrooms have City/Downtown views and are accompanied by a full bathroom with bathtub/shower combination and double vanity. This property also provides a bonus space on the lower level - great for a home gym, office or media area. Hardwood floors throughout, double pane widows, custom window treatments, new carpet on the stairs, one car garage  and abundant storage. Situated on a coveted block, 49 Woodland is just minutes from the many shops & restaurants of Cole Valley, Sutro Reserve, UCSF, and Goldman Tennis Center.

Situated on large corner lot, this fully remodeled Mid Century Modern home has 3 bedrooms, 4 bathrooms and an open concept main living area with Chef-grade kitchen, center island and Thermador appliances (six burner range, refrigerator, dishwasher, microwave and wine storage). Well proportioned bedrooms, motorized shades, and one comes with a Murphy Bed, allowing it to double as an office. The primary bedroom boasts 2 bathrooms with design-grade fixtures, shower, soaking tub, Toto Washlet toilets, floating vanities, and heated towel warmer. There are two large closets, with custom built cabinetry. A separate ADU doubles as a family room with full kitchen, that leads directly out to a professionally landscaped, fenced, low maintenance back yard with drip irrigation. A wood deck area for dining and lounging, and a hot tub make for great indoor/ outdoor living. An over-sized garage has room for two cars and storage.Modern updates include: tankless hot water heater, recessed lighting, full size W/D, triple paned windows, smart home technology, keyless entry system, security cameras, central heat and AC (main level). Buyers will appreciate this rare, well designed home with overlooks of Glen Canyon, a short distance to Noe Valley and the Castro, and easy access to the freeways.

This Mission Dolores/Dolores Heights condo has it all!  2 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, 1 car independent garage parking, in-unit washer/dryer, and private balcony. Constructed in 2003, this condo has a great open floor plan, gas burning fireplace, generous sized closets, recessed lighting, and crown moldings. The kitchen is equipped with stainless appliances, including a gas range, dishwasher, microwave and refrigerator. The very spacious primary bedroom has a large closet, bathroom with soaking tub, and dual sinks. The second bedroom is versatile and can be used for guests, as an office or as desired. The unit has been freshly painted. Best of all, it's steps from the vibrant food and boutique scene along the Valencia Street corridor and 2 blocks to Mission Dolores Park.  Overall, it's a great buy in a great neighborhood!

Rare opportunity to own a home in the highly sought-after Inner Sunset neighborhood with the potential to customize renovations to your liking.  Natural light streams through the windows in the main level of this home which features a living room, a separate dining room, two bedrooms, sunroom and a split bathroom.    Downstairs includes high ceilings, offering unlimited possibilities for expansion. The backyard includes a spacious yard for you to transform into various options such as a beautiful garden, a play area for children, or an area for outdoor gatherings.  Conveniently located to Sunset area schools, transportation, shopping and popular restaurants.

Breathtaking fully remodeled property located in the scenic city of San Francisco!  This exquisite residence boasts views of the iconic Golden Gate Bridge & the majestic Sutro Tower, providing an unparalleled backdrop for luxurious living. As you step into this remarkable home, you will notice the meticulous attention to detail. The kitchen features marble counters & is equipped with top-of-the-line appliances. The white oak floors lend an air of sophistication, while designer finishes add a touch of modern elegance. With a total of 5 bedrooms & 4.5 bathrooms, this property offers ample space for both relaxation & entertainment. The high ceilings create an airy & spacious ambiance, while deck spaces on every level allow for seamless indoor-outdoor living. The beautifully maintained outdoor space offers a sanctuary for relaxation & entertainment, complete with lush greenery & a charming atmosphere. This property is a true masterpiece in one of San Francisco's most desirable locations.

Incredible Location and first time on the market in 50 years! This gorgeous, split level 2 bed, 1 bath, 1,360 square foot home is located in the hugely desirable Lakeside neighborhood.  Pride of ownership together with tasteful updates, make this 1939 construction seem modern and new. Beautifully refinished hardwood floors on the main level shine with all the natural light this home allows in.  Fresh paint throughout and brand new carpet both upstairs, as well as in the bonus room down.  Bonus room down features an updated full bath, access to both garage and backyard, in addition to separate entrance capabilities.  Newer kitchen complete with breakfast area, which leads to the simple, but nicely landscaped backyard.  Formal dining room adjacent to breakfast area allows for an easy flow to the home, as well as, making it great for entertaining. 1 car garage with additional off-street spot in the driveway, plus ample street parking, Ocean and 19th Avenues less than a block away, steps to MUNI access, walk to Stonestown, SF State and West Portal.  Easy access to any and all conveniences make this a true gem in San Francisco.

This newly renovated top floor 2BD/2BA condo features an open plan living area w/wood burning fireplace & dramatic wall of windows, & city views. Sliding glass doors open to a large private deck. The kitchen has been remodeled w/custom cabinetry & granite countertops w/bar, stainless steel appliances, including Viking stove & hood, KitchenAid refrigerator, & Miele dishwasher. A skylight above the kitchen floods the room with natural light. The large primary bedroom with ample closet space has an en-suite bath w/shower over tub & Carrera style tile surround, custom vanity with quartz countertops, & skylight overhead. The second bedroom also has generous closet space and an en-suite bath, has nice southerly views & direct access to the large deck. The guest bath, accessible from the second bedroom or hallway, has a large custom vanity w/quartz counters, skylight & separate room with walk-in shower & custom Carrera style tile & separate linen closet. Add'l features include newly installed engineered hardwood flooring, formal entry w/skylight & coat closet, double paned windows, fresh paint, common laundry, deeded storage & 1 car pkg. Condo is ideally situated at the intersection of Nob and Russian Hill, steps from many popular shops and restaurants on vibrant Polk Street.

Price Improvement! Located in The Beacon, a luxurious full amenity building in desirable Mission Bay neighborhood. This meticulously maintained residence ensures a lifestyle of comfort and convenience. 2 BD/2BA, bright and inviting condo with open floorplan. Large windows flood the interior with natural sunlight. Expansive 240 sq. ft. terrace, where you can relish in indoor/outdoor living and unlock endless possibilities for relaxation and entertainment. Updated kitchen featuring granite countertops and stainless-steel appliances. The high-end French Oak plank flooring adds a touch of elegance to the space, while the in-unit washer and dryer provide convenience. The Beacon offers a level of luxury living, with a 24-hour concierge and an array of amenities, including, a heated outdoor pool and spa, club lounge, gym, business center, and outdoor dog park. A designated spot in the parking garage ensures convenient hassle-free parking. Perfectly situated in an urban haven, this condo is just steps away from groceries, restaurants, boutiques, luxury bowling alley and highway access. Explore the thriving Mission Bay area, where the renowned Chase Center and Oracle Park awaits. Commuting is a breeze with Muni, bus lines, and Caltrain all within one block, making it a commuter's dream.

Located in prime Noe Valley, mere blocks from 24th St., your private oasis awaits. Flooded with light from windows on 3 sides, this condominium offers a beautifully flowing layout updated with top notch finishes while still maintaining beautiful classical details. Two bedrooms and 2-full bathrooms with ample living space, and a shared outdoor space for your morning coffee or WFH. With gorgeous hardwoods, beautiful light throughout, an updated eat-in kitchen, and a recently updated primary bathroom, you're sure to fall in love with this charming unit! The eat-in kitchen is dreamy with newer stainless steel appliances, beautiful marble counter tops and updated overhead lighting. One side-by-side parking space in the garage with plenty of storage, and your own laundry seals the deal. Perfectly situated between Noe Valley's 24th Street and Valencia St/Mission restaurants and shopping including Novy, Beretta, Firefly and Saru. Close to Dolores Park and the Noe Valley Recreation Center and easy access to J-Church, multiple Muni buses, and 280/101 make commuting a breeze!  This home is a do not miss opportunity to be in one of the most sought-after pockets of San Francisco!

The residence at 2405 Folsom St No. 5 is a spacious and modern home in a vibrant neighborhood. The three-level home was built in 2008 and has been nicely updated since then. The floor plan is generous and includes two terraces that provide plenty of natural light and space, making it feel like a single-family home. On the first floor, there is a living, dining area and kitchen that runs from the front to the back of the residence. This area also includes an attached terrace. The second level is just as bright and spacious and features two ensuite bedrooms and a laundry room. Finally, the third level is dedicated entirely to the primary suite, which includes a large spa-like bathroom, walk-in closet, wet bar, and a large outdoor terrace. In addition to the ample living space, the residence also comes with two car parking. Overall, this is a comfortable and convenient living space in one of the best locations in the city.

**Last unit remaining!** The ParksideSF features 13 generous condos ranging from one to three bedrooms. Unit 103 is located on the 3rd floor. Extensively updated, this unit offers San Francisco living at its finest, at every step. The updated kitchen has everything you need: gorgeous porcelain slab countertops and backsplash, a statement waterfall breakfast bar, modern cabinetry, and high-end stainless steel appliances from Thermador, Fisher & Paykel and Bosch. Parking and storage is available for every unit. Elevator in the building and secured bike room.

Open house Saturday July 5th, 12PM - 4PM!

Two story house, 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths plus multiple bonus rooms! New kitchen, updated bathrooms, hardwood floor, fresh paint. In-unit washer/dryer is included. Everything brand new! One block from Golden Gate park and Ocean beach. Couple steps away from Judah St & La Playa St Muni. One car garage + drive way parking. Shares backyard with the ADU in the back. Not furnished. Lower level (1 bed, 1 bath, bonus rooms) has own entrance.

Small dog or cat is welcome. Income must be at least 2x rent. $6000 deposit. Tenants pays electricity/gas and water. Trash pickup is included in rent. $35/adult application fee.

Showing by appointment after work hours or any time over weekends. Please text/email with your name, phone number, number of occupants and monthly income to arrange showing.

Introducing an amazing property in San Francisco's coveted Outer Sunset. This stunning property has 2 buildings totaling 2,389 SF on one parcel. Both buildings have been completely remodeled. The front is a beautiful 2-level house with 2 entrances on each level. The main home has 4bd/2 full + 1 half baths, with separate living areas on each level, and w/d. The rear home has 3 bd/1.5 baths, + bonus room, w/d, and is currently generating an impressive $3,950/month in rental income. Located just 100 yds. from the N Judah Muni and nestled just one block away from the breathtaking Golden Gate Park and Ocean Beach, this area is perfect for outdoor enthusiasts, offering a wide range of activities such as strolling on the beach, bike riding, surfing, and horseback riding in Golden Gate Park. The vibrant neighborhood commercial area, complete with the famous Java Beach Cafe, offers an unbeatable location.

A beautiful light-filled corner residence,facing the pool in the sought-after North Waterfront neighborhood. Peek-a-boo views of coit tower and downtown. The living room opens to a large sunny deck facing the gardens and pool. Beautiful wood-burning fireplace. High ceilings. New appliances, carpets, and fresh paint. The spacious primary suite looks out to the gardens and the financial district and has a huge walk-in closet.  Amenities include a 24/7-hour Security/Doorman, Pool, Spa, Landscaped gardens, and conference & Club room.  Come home to the easy lifestyle living at 101 Lombard.

World-Class views of Golden Gate Bridge, Bay Bridge, San Francisco Skyline and beyond from a premiere Russian Hill doorman high-rise, The Summit! The versatile floor plan was created by combining two units #2903 and #2905. The signature floor-to-ceiling glass walls of this ultra-luxury high-floor Northeast corner residence frame incredibly sky-high 3-bridge, 4-county views from the Golden Gate Bridge to Bay Bridge, from the San Francisco Skyline to the Marin Headlands and beyond. Floating high above the Magical City-by-The-Bay'' this gracious residence enjoys postcard-like views of San Francisco's world-renowned landmarks and the ever-changing beauty of the Bay    Featuring generous entertaining spaces, 2 large bedrooms plus den, 2 full bathrooms, step-out terrace and a timeless contemporary design, this is a wonderful home to enjoy a quintessentially urban lifestyle in one of the City's most desirable and historic residential neighborhoods.

Sophisticated 2BR/1BA condo in the heart of Upper Fillmore! Enter your new home through a tiered fragrant courtyard with chirping birds and awash in all-day sun. Private patio entrance invites lazing around in a secluded sitting area. Inside, excellent floorplan spreads out across one level and includes en-suite primary BR, second BR, LR/DR combination and efficient kitchen with pass-through. Classy upgrades like custom wood cabinets and stone countertops in kitchen and bath, stainless appliances, wood-burning FP with stone surround and hearth, and built-in storage cabinet in living room put this home a cut above ordinary condos. Bay window in DR creates more space for sumptuous dinners, and tree-shaded balcony off living room is your own private roost for watching what's happening on Fillmore Street. In-unit W/D, generous closets, pet-friendly building, one-car deeded garage parking, new carpet and fresh paint make this home truly move-in ready. Central location offers close proximity to exciting shops, cafes, restaurants, boutiques, farmer's markets and entertainment venues, as well as numerous transportation choices and quick access to downtown and 101. Ditch your diet and visit the Fillmore Bakeshop downstairs for fresh croissants, cookies and pies. This is home.

Stunning rarely available ocean front views from this 3 bedroom/2 bath unit in a boutique building.    Imagine relaxing by the sea as you watch the sun set over the ocean, strolling along the beach, surfing or parasailing the iconic Ocean Beach waves!    Gourmet renovated kitchen, with recessed lighting, stainless steel appliances, fresh paint and new flooring throughout allow for endless entertaining.    The generous living room has a huge bay window facing the Pacific Ocean, allowing for spectacular sunsets over the sea.    The spacious primary suite includes an ensuite bath, 2 closets and a garden view, with 2 additional generous bedrooms.  In unit side-by side laundry.    Set in an established neighborhood, where neighbors share a love of the ocean, this is truly a rare find.    Shared yard.  Garage: 1 car garage parking and 1 parking permit for the private street.  This exceptional location is close to Golden Gate Park, Sutro Heights, Lands End hiking trails, grocery,  MUNI, the VA Medical Center and the many shops and restaurants on Balboa Street.

100 Judah is a grand & stately home with over 4,000 square feet of interior space that graces the corner of Judah & 6th Ave in the prime Inner Sunset. Filled w/ history, it has remained in the same family for over 60 yrs. The classic Edwardian architecture provides both timeless elegance + an ideal floor plan. Although it is definitely a fixer'', it doesn't require an expansion/major floor plan changes for it to be the epic landmark home of your dreams. The foyer divides the main floor w/ a spacious living rm on the right & dining rm on the left. Both rooms feature fireplaces & built-ins. A large kitchen & laundry room run parallel to the dining rm, while a sunroom leads to a staircase to the garden. The 2nd floor has 3 bedrms & 1 full bath, while the 3rd floor has 2 bedrms, a 2nd full bath + an extra room. The bedrms are generous in size & filled w/ light. The baths need updating but provide an opportunity for customization. A staircase from the main level leads to a full basement offering potential for playrm, fitness, storage, etc. A separate garage provides parking/storage. This large Edwardian home in a phenomenal neighborhood boasts square footage + a terrific floor plan. It requires a fair amount of TLC but its natural beauty & undeniable potential justify the investment.

Updated Outer Sunset home conveniently located just half block from Noriega Street restaurants & shops, both Noriega St & 46th Ave public transit, Ocean Beach, & West Sunset Playground. Top floor features living room, dining area, updated kitchen with breakfast area, two bedrooms, and bath. Ground floor offers additional room added in 1964 (On record in 3R, but with no additional info on status) and one large car parking with additional space for storage. Partial ocean views from the top floor! Upgrades include kitchen and bath remodel several years ago, new luxury vinyl floor over existing hardwood floor on the top floor, new luxury vinyl floor on ground floor room, and new interior & exterior paint! Huge flat yard!

Bursting with authentic SF charm, this 3 bdrm Parkside gem is the perfect place to call home. The center of the home, accessible via French Doors from the kitchen, is a sun-filled, usable center patio providing cozy outdoor space for morning coffee and an area to entertain guests. Gleaming hardwood floors greet you upon arrival & flow continuously through the voluminous living room w/fireplace, formal dining room & to 2 generously sized bedrooms & beautifully remodeled bathroom. The remodeled Chef's kitchen is equipped with top of the line Bosch appliances, ample counter space & tons of storage. The lower level features an extensive primary bedroom with a large walk-in closet, renovated full bathroom, direct access to the low-maintenance sunny backyard & enormous 2 car garage with extra storage space & laundry. Walkable to numerous parks including Pine Lake Park & Stern Grove, Ocean Beach, countless neighborhood restaurants & easy access to Muni all contribute to this A+ location.

Stunning, fully detached house with the desirable layout of 3 bedrooms on one level on a coveted block in West Portal - a cherished San Francisco neighborhood. This updated home not only has a great layout and sought-after location it also has an impressive kitchen, gorgeous natural light and curb appeal. The main level features a welcoming entryway, large living room with a gas fireplace, formal dining room and chef's kitchen with a nice-sized breakfast nook. Only a few steps up to the upper level are its 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms. The primary bedroom is spacious and comfortable. The lower level offers a big bonus space that can be wonderful for entertaining, working from home and working out. The sizable garage has interior access and a lot of storage space. There is 2 car parking in the garage and 1 car parking in the driveway. Beautiful hardwood floors and period details enhance the character of the home. Freshly painted interior and exterior. Low maintenance front yard and backyard complete this property. Near the heart of West Portal Village and its numerous popular restaurants, cafes and shops. Conveniently located by Muni, Stonestown, Stern Grove and schools. Short drive to the freeway, Lake Merced, Fort Funston and Ocean Beach. This special house checks off the boxes.

Welcome to 458 Mangels Avenue, a charming Edwardian, nestled on a tranquil street in the Sunnyside Neighborhood! The home is detached on three and a half sides and has a bright interior that includes a spacious kitchen, and formal dining room, two bedrooms, a Jack-and-Jill bathroom and a comfortable living room. There are large doors from the kitchen that lead to a deck and patio area in the serene garden---making it a wonderful indoor/outdoor home. It has a basement with ample storage space and garage for one vehicle, as well as a driveway space for another vehicle.   Features of note include: original period details, hardwood floors, a box-beam ceiling in the dining room, dual-paned windows, a claw foot tub, a bonus sleeping loft in the rear bedroom, original built-in bookshelves and China cabinet, 10 foot ceilings, tasteful lighting fixtures, a landscaped front and rear garden, located adjacent to Sunnyside park and playground, the home is also close to transportation, dining and shopping on Monterey Blvd. Ocean Ave. and Glen Park Village.

Welcome to this charming and spacious single-family home on wide, easy-to-drive-through Holyoke Street! 2 bedrooms and 1 bathroom on the main level with a large living room plus fireplace, a formal dining room, a kitchen with breakfast nook and plenty of cabinets. Lower level has 2 bedrooms, a permitted bathroom and a galley kitchen - easily functional as two separate units. The house has hardwood floors throughout, a skylight in the hallway, and a one-car garage with washer/dryer. The backyard is perfect for entertaining and sipping your favorite cabernet under the gazebo, accessible from both levels. City approvals to build a backyard deck ready in hand too. Conveniently located near San Bruno Avenue row of shops, restaurants, John McLaren Park, schools, and public transportation. Close to Silver Avenue, 101 and 280 for easy access to downtown San Francisco and the Peninsula. Don't miss this opportunity to own this lovely home in a desirable neighborhood!

This California Bungalow captures views of urban hillsides, San Bruno Mt and coastal landscapes.  Enter from the semi glass-enclosed front porch into the foyer-living areas with built-ins and gas fireplace.  An abundance of light fills these rooms through eight windows spanning the full width of the property.  A full bath with a cast iron bathtub and primary bedroom lie off a hallway from the foyer.  An adjacent doorway in the living area leads to an open kitchen-dining room with access to a bedroom with half bath and the upper deck and laundry room.  With coastal views and westerly sunsets, the lower deck leads down to the lush gardens and sitting area.  Situated on an expansive flat lot perched a few feet above the sidewalk, street and park, the Bungalow faces east and has a front yard lined by a picket fence.  On the other side of the yard, a path follows along the side of the house through a wooden gate to the backyard and decks.  The entranceways to the detached garage and the lower level with two bonus rooms and a full bath are along this pathway.  This property appeals to both those seeking move-in ready or a visionary's canvas, all with its original character of a classic 1916 SF Bungalow intact.

NEW PRICE! COME & GET IT!  Light, volume and location in this rarely available 1st floor home! Yerba Buena Lofts has always been celebrated for it's architecture, and this loft features all of the signature touches from starchitect Stanley Saitowitz: dramatic walls of glass, exposed concrete for a cool industrial vibe, and a private outdoor terrace. In addition, you'll find a host of thoughtful upgrades throughout. A private entrance from Folsom makes this uniquely versatile. Soaring ceilings add drama to the open living room and kitchen, and upstairs the sleeping area has a luxurious amount of closet space. Building amenities include: 24-Hour security, secure lobby, on-site management, and a full-time engineer & maintenance staff. Nearly perfect WalkScore means the ultimate in city convenience. Whole Foods, Metreon, Trader Joes, Financial District, Ball Park, FiDi & Embarcadero all at your doorstep. A private parking spot plus in-unit laundry complete the package.

3 bedroom, 2 bath, 1 parking Below Market Rate (BMR) housing opportunity available at 100% Area Median Income (AMI). Maximum income for 3 people = $124,700; 4 = $138,550; 5 = $149,650; 6 = $160,700, etc. Must be 1st-time homebuyer & income eligible. Unit available thru the Mayor's Office of Housing and Community Development (MOHCD) & subject to resale controls, monitoring & other restrictions. Unit will be listed on DAHLIA, the SF Housing Portal (https://housing.sfgov.org) starting on the application date, Thursday, March 9th, 2023. Visit https://housing.sfgov.org for application & program info. Application, loan pre-approval, and homebuyer education verification due on Thursday, March 30th, 2023 at 5:00 PM. Open house times Saturday, March 18 - 12-2pm, Tuesday, March 21 - 2-4pm, Friday, March 24 - 5-7pm.

44-46 Morrell Street is a duplex in the bustling Nob Hill neighborhood of San Francisco, adjacent to Russian Hill. The building features two units needing some renovations and a charming yard and laundry shed in the rear. This property presents an opportunity for an investor to modernize the units and rent them at market rate or for an owner to occupy the building. Nob Hill is a historic and affluent neighborhood known for its luxurious mansions, upscale hotels, and stunning views of the city and bay. Some of San Francisco's most iconic landmarks, including the famous cable cars, Grace Cathedral, and the Fairmont Hotel, are located here.

This elegant and luxurious condo overlooks a serene manicured courtyard and presents an incredible sense of calm and spaciousness. The well-appointed and flexible open layout is ideal for entertainment and provides an abundance of living space. Extensively renovated, Unit 307 features European white oak wood floors, a beautifully modern kitchen with Carrara marble countertops and stainless steel appliances, high-end range, wood-burning fireplace in the living room, renovated modern bathroom with marble tile surround, and private patio with barbecue space. This beautifully maintained elevator building features secure garage parking, updated contemporary lobby, shared sauna, and incredible landscaped private courtyard where pets can play and residents can enjoy reading benches which sit beneath mature trees and open sky. Unit 307 also includes a large private storage unit, which is spacious enough to store bicycles and large sports equipment. With a WalkScore of 99, living at 1440 Broadway is ideal in both convenience and ease. Located in the gorgeous and highly desirable Nob Hill/Polk Gulch neighborhood, Unit 307 is just moments from an abundance of neighborhood amenities, gourmet cafes, fine restaurants, shops, parks, public transportation and much more.  1440broadway307.com

Designed to respond to the needs of the contemporary San Francisco Lifestyle - ORAN delivers the latest innovations in quality and environmentally conscious design - supported by enriching amenities, including an expansive entertainment view deck with outdoor lounges and fire pits, an Olive grove, open-air gymnasium, barbecue, and a dog run. Situated in the center of one of the city's most culturally diverse and vibrant neighborhoods, the architecturally striking building is an urban oasis in every sense. Health and wellness take center stage at ORAN, the first multiunit residential building offered in San Francisco with individual GPS ionizing systemsthe technology trusted in schools, airports, and healthcare facilities to help improve indoor air. Residence 608 is a remarkable 2 bedroom & 2 bath corner penthouse with views. Featuring a streamlined kitchen, dedicated ensuite bath, and in-unit laundry, this home is replete with every amenity you expectand some unexpected. The thoughtful details, and elevator, extend from the roof's landscaped view deck to the parking level and dedicated bike storage. Latch touchless entry and Luxor Locker delivery concierge are included.  ORAN-Wellness Elevated. Photos of similar unit; finishes and layout may vary.

Don't miss this grand European style residence in a luxury Edwardian era property. Unit E is one of the largest units in a nine unit building. With some vintage details throughout, unit #E offers the new owner an opportunity to create one's own special space while adding value to a classic. The north facing home is brightened with light through banks of casement windows in the dining room, spacious living room, and master bedroom. The MB, with its walk-in closet, includes a lovely alcove seating area. Off the kitchen is a pantry area, quarter bath, and laundry room. Parking for one car on a space rotational schedule is included.

Want to live in the best neighborhood in SF!  Pacific Heights is the place to live!  This 1700 sq ft Condo is steps away from Lafayette Park! The Park has tennis courts, picnic areas and a doggie park. Whole Foods is a blk away. Shops and restaurants on Fillmore are all walking distance.  1700 sq ft of Pacific Heights elegance that has modern upgrades. All three bedrooms are facing a beautiful courtyard. The best floor plan in the entire building. Great place for entertaining. Beautiful original wood floors throughout. Very peaceful and quiet since it's not on the street side of the building.    Juliet Balconies off the master and the dining room.  9FT Ceilings. Both bathrooms have been remodeled.    Private washer and dryer area with Bosch Appliances. High end kitchen appliances including a wine refrigerator. This beautiful condo also has a very large, assigned storage space plus additional storage.  Leased parking (24/7) is a block away across from Whole Foods for $380 per month.  Plenty of street parking with permit. Permit per year is $165 per year.  Pet friendly. Text Eddy at 415.606.5043 for private showing.  Seller Negotiable.  Offers due by Sun, July 16th night by 9pm.  Seller rent $7000 the condo on 7/18/23 if no offers.

Opportunity knocks!! A blank canvas for new owners to update to their liking and enjoy the ocean views from this bright natural light filled corner lot Sunset District home. 2 bedrooms and 1 bath upstairs, large bright living room, kitchen and dining area with great views of the ocean. Bonus room downstairs, laundry and attached garage and sideyard for play. The location is awesome, great schools, walk to ocean beach, restaurants, transportation and shopping. Safeway just 5 blocks away.

Outstanding Westwood Park Beauty is nestled on one of the best blocks in this charming neighborhood! This traditional family hm has been beautifully refurbished w/Custom Paint, Newly Refinished Hrwd Flrs, Updated Windows & Elegant Lighting. Welcoming foyer opens to gracious FLR w/handsome Cr Molding & Magnificent Stone Frplc. Inviting FDR overlooks the peaceful backyd & flows seamlessly to a stylish Kitchen w/quality SS Appliances, Granite Cntrs & Wood Cabinetry. French Doors open to a quaint brick patio perfect for outdoor BBQ'ing. Excellent Laundry Rm w/SxS W/D completes this area. Two Spacious BD's each w/ample closets & one accessing an ensuite Full Tiled BA w/Shower Over Tub. Top Fl 2nd Lev provides stunning light-filled Primary Suite w/Full BA, Dressing Area, Walk-in Closet & grand additional storage quarters. Large Garage w/numerous Storage Cabinets & private secluded rm perfect for home office. Walk to public transportation, shops & restaurants.Offers Reviewed 7/18 @ 11AM.

Incredibly charming Marina style home awaits your personal touch. Opportunity knocks with this delightful diamond in the rough positioned on a deep lot, with over 1,350 square feet of living space, expansive garage, and garden below! The home boasts a traditional layout offering a welcoming living room with a wall of south-facing windows and a wood-burning fireplace, adjacent formal dining room, vintage kitchen with breakfast nook and Wedgewood stove, original bathroom, two good-sized bedrooms, and sunroom overlooking the low maintenance garden below. Interior access from the central hallway leads you down to the spacious garage with room to park multiple cars, laundry area with full size washer & dryer, and room for plenty of storage. Bring your contractor, color palette & imagination because this is the one you've been waiting for! Ideal location on the border of Sunnyside, with close proximity to Glen Park Village shopping and restaurants, Glen Canyon Park, Ocean Avenue corridor, public transit/BART, highways 101 & 280, and so much more!

Modern and meticulously maintained two-bedroom home with magical views located on one of the most desirable streets on the western slope of Bernal Heights! Behind the Mid-century facade is a contemporary and inviting floor plan that opens to gorgeous wood floors and a wall of windows accentuating the magnificent panoramic views and illuminating the living area with an abundance of natural light. The living/dining area is on the same level with a fireplace, adjacent to the private deck and tastefully updated gourmet kitchen with modern appliances offering views from every angle. There are two bedrooms with ample closet space that are located at the front of the flat, perfectly positioned for privacy, and an updated bathroom with spa-like finishes. One independent, side-by-side parking space in the large garage, along with deeded storage space, common area storage space, and solar panels.  Don't miss this special home that is close to shops, cafes, world class dining, playgrounds, public transportation, HWY 101/280 and more!

Fixer or Development Potential on Historic Ringold Street. There are Four Vacant Units, split between separate Front and Rear Buildings. The Upper Unit in the Front Building has 2 Bedrooms, a Living Room, Bathroom and Eat-In Kitchen. The Lower Unit in the Front Building can be used as either a 1 or 2 bedroom and has an Eat-In Kitchen and Bathroom.  The Rear Building consists of two 1 Bedroom Units, each with an Entry Foyer, Dining Room and Bathroom. Large Basement under Front Building and Smaller Storage Closets under Rear Building.  New Roof on Front Building in 2021.  There is deferred maintenance in all units and common areas. Located up on 21st Street in San Francisco, this home is a true gem representing a piece of the city''s wonderful history. Tucked away in two rows of Victorians, this property features prime examples of an era that has long since passed. This is a grand-style Victorian home that stands out for its outstanding pedigree. Built in the late 1800s, this property lived through the 1906 and 1989 earthquakes and several other tremors over the years. This fact alone speaks volumes about the durability and sturdiness of this exceptional property. This home has been in loving hands since 1892 and has even served as the consular residence of a Pacific Island Nation. Over the past half-century, it has been lovingly restored and improved upon, making it a wonderful and unique place to call home. 3847 21st Street offers an exceptional floor plan that includes two ample and sumptuous floors of living space along with a darling attic bedroom with a window overlooking San Francisco above, and a workshop, sauna, and a two-car garage on the ground floor below. This home has plenty of room for improvement and development as well. Rarely can you find a property that offers such a perfect combination of space, functionality, and charm.

Built in approximately 1893 by capitalist Andrew B. McCreery, and sold a year later to Burr Nobel, 611 Baker Street epitomizes the grand San Francisco Victorian of years gone by. Remarkably, this stunning property remained within the original owner's family for nearly six decades, while the current owners, the third in line, resided at 611 Baker for nearly 50 years. Now, after a remarkable 130-year history, this magnificent Queen Anne Victorian eagerly awaits its fourth owner, presenting a rare opportunity to become a part of its enduring legacy.  In nearly original condition, this home retains its architectural splendor, including a lower unit garden apartment and a two-level carriage house situated at the rear of the lot. The stately bi-level owner's unit is characterized by its exquisite wood floors, ornate woodwork, and intricate moldings that grace every corner. On the main level, you'll find a traditional double parlor and a formal dining room, each separated by original pocket doors, adding to the timeless charm and elegance of the home.
